<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title><![CDATA[Spring]]></title><description><![CDATA[Level up your Java code and explore what Spring can do for you.]]></description><link>https://spring.io</link><generator>GatsbyJS</generator><lastBuildDate>Fri, 13 Jun 2025 00:39:14 GMT</lastBuildDate><item><title><![CDATA[Spring Framework 7.0.0-M6 available now]]></title><link>https://spring.io/blog/2025/06/12/spring-framework-7-0-0-M6-available-now</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://spring.io/blog/2025/06/12/spring-framework-7-0-0-M6-available-now</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[bclozel]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 12 Jun 2025 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;On behalf of the team and everyone who has contributed, I am pleased to announce a new milestone for the next Spring Framework generation.
The M6 continues delivering new features and refinements on top of &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/blog/2025/01/23/spring-framework-7-0-0-M1-available-now&quot;&gt;7.0.0-M1&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/blog/2025/02/13/spring-framework-7-0-0-M2-available-now&quot;&gt;7.0.0-M2&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/blog/2025/03/13/spring-framework-7-0-0-M3-available-now&quot;&gt;7.0.0-M3&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/blog/2025/04/17/spring-framework-7-0-0-M4-available-now&quot;&gt;7.0.0-M4&lt;/a&gt; and  &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/blog/2025/05/15/spring-framework-7-0-0-M5-available-now&quot;&gt;7.0.0-M5&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve made lots of refinements on features delivered in previous milestones, but we also have a new feature that we would like to share.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;retry-support-in-spring-core&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#retry-support-in-spring-core&quot; aria-label=&quot;retry support in spring core permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Retry support in Spring Core&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have been working on the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-retry&quot;&gt;Spring Retry project&lt;/a&gt; for a very long time.
The Spring team decided that it was time to trim unnecessary features, revisit some of its API and merge the resulting work into the &quot;spring-core&quot; module of Spring Framework.
This new Retry support is located in the &lt;code&gt;org.springframework.core.retry&lt;/code&gt; package, we will update the reference documentation soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the meantime, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-batch/issues/4868&quot;&gt;Spring projects like Spring Batch are already working on using this in place of spring-retry&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;and-much-more&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#and-much-more&quot; aria-label=&quot;and much more permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;And much more!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As usual, you can check &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/releases/tag/v7.0.0-M6&quot;&gt;the detailed changelog&lt;/a&gt; for more details
and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/wiki/Spring-Framework-7.0-Release-Notes&quot;&gt;read the global 7.0 release notes for upgrade concerns&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;7.0.0-M6 is now available from &lt;a href=&quot;https://repo.spring.io&quot;&gt;https://repo.spring.io&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/blog/2025/01/21/milestones-to-central&quot;&gt;Maven Central&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/projects/spring-framework/&quot;&gt;Project Page&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework&quot;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues&quot;&gt;Issues&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/reference/&quot;&gt;Documentation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Spring Framework 6.1.21 and 6.2.8 releases fix CVE-2025-41234]]></title><link>https://spring.io/blog/2025/06/12/spring-framework-6-1-21-and-6-2-8-releases-fix-cve-2025-41234</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://spring.io/blog/2025/06/12/spring-framework-6-1-21-and-6-2-8-releases-fix-cve-2025-41234</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[bclozel]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 12 Jun 2025 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;On behalf of the team and everyone who has contributed, I am pleased to announce that Spring Framework &lt;code&gt;6.1.21&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;6.2.8&lt;/code&gt; are available now.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spring Framework &lt;code&gt;6.1.21&lt;/code&gt; ships with &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/releases/tag/v6.1.21&quot;&gt;3 fixes and documentation improvements&lt;/a&gt;. This version will be shipped next week with Spring Boot &lt;code&gt;3.3.13&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spring Framework &lt;code&gt;6.2.8&lt;/code&gt; ships with &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/releases/tag/v6.2.8&quot;&gt;39 fixes and documentation improvements&lt;/a&gt;. This version will be shipped next week with Spring Boot &lt;code&gt;3.4.7&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;3.5.1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;cve-2025-41234&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#cve-2025-41234&quot; aria-label=&quot;cve 2025 41234 permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;CVE-2025-41234:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The releases address &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/security/cve-2025-41234&quot;&gt;CVE-2025-41234&lt;/a&gt; for RFD Attack via “Content-Disposition” Header Sourced from Request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open source support for Spring Framework 5.3.x and 6.0.x generations has ended, and this is our last OSS release for the 6.1.x generation, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/projects/spring-framework#support&quot;&gt;our support page for more information&lt;/a&gt;.
This fix has been applied to the 6.0.29 commercial release, available now.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are not a commercial customer, &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/projects/spring-framework/#support&quot;&gt;please consider upgrading to an open source supported version&lt;/a&gt; at your earliest convenience.
Commercial customers using Spring Boot 2.7, 3.1, or 3.2 can make use of Spring Boot Hotfix releases 3.1.17.1, and 3.2.15.1. Releases are available now on the Spring commercial artifact repository and can be accessed with a &lt;a href=&quot;https://enterprise.spring.io&quot;&gt;Spring Enterprise Subscription&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/projects/spring-framework/&quot;&gt;Project Page&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework&quot;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues&quot;&gt;Issues&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/reference/&quot;&gt;Documentation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[A Bootiful Podcast: The legendary Daniel Garnier-Moiroux on security, AI, MCP, and more]]></title><link>https://spring.io/blog/2025/06/12/a-bootiful-podcast-daniel-garnier-moiroux</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://spring.io/blog/2025/06/12/a-bootiful-podcast-daniel-garnier-moiroux</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[joshlong]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 12 Jun 2025 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;Hi, Spring fans! In this installment I talk to the legendary Daniel Garnier-Moiroux on security, AI, MCP, and more, recorded live at Devoxx UK 2025.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;iframe title=&quot;The legendary Daniel Garnier-Moiroux on security, AI, MCP, and more&quot; allowtransparency=&quot;true&quot; height=&quot;300&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; style=&quot;border: none; min-width: min(100%, 430px);height:300px;&quot; scrolling=&quot;no&quot; data-name=&quot;pb-iframe-player&quot; src=&quot;https://www.podbean.com/player-v2/?from=embed&amp;i=pmv5a-18d4242-pb&amp;square=1&amp;share=1&amp;download=1&amp;fonts=Arial&amp;skin=1&amp;font-color=&amp;rtl=0&amp;logo_link=&amp;btn-skin=7&amp;size=300&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Spring Tools 4.31.0 released]]></title><link>https://spring.io/blog/2025/06/11/spring-tools-4-31-0-released</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://spring.io/blog/2025/06/11/spring-tools-4-31-0-released</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[martinlippert]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 11 Jun 2025 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;On behalf of the team and everyone who has contributed, I am pleased to announce the 4.31.0 release of the Spring Tools
for Visual Studio Code, Eclipse and Theia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;important-highlights&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#important-highlights&quot; aria-label=&quot;important highlights permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;important highlights&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Spring Boot)&lt;/em&gt; early access preview: support for Spring Data AOT repositories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Spring Boot)&lt;/em&gt; support for upgrades to Spring Boot 3.5 (build files and properties only)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Spring Boot)&lt;/em&gt; support for hierarchical document symbols in both VSCode and Eclipse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;updates-to-the-spring-tools-for-eclipse-distribution&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#updates-to-the-spring-tools-for-eclipse-distribution&quot; aria-label=&quot;updates to the spring tools for eclipse distribution permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;updates to the Spring Tools for Eclipse distribution&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;updated to Eclipse 2025-06 release (&lt;a href=&quot;https://eclipseide.org/release/noteworthy/&quot;&gt;new and noteworthy&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;support for Java 24 included by default&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Detailed changes can be found in the release notes: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/sts4/releases/tag/4.31.0.RELEASE&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/sts4/releases/tag/4.31.0.RELEASE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;downloads&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#downloads&quot; aria-label=&quot;downloads permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;downloads&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To download the distribution for Eclipse and find links to the marketplace entries for Visual Studio Code and Theia, please go visit:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spring Tools: &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/tools/&quot;&gt;https://spring.io/tools/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spring Tools 4.32.0 is scheduled to be released in late July 2025.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item></channel></rss>